'''Roberto Sandoval Castañeda''' (born 15 November 1969) is a [[Mexican people|Mexican]] politician affiliated with the [[Institutional Revolutionary Party]]. From 2011 to 2017 he served as [[Governor of Nayarit]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Roberto Sandoval toma protesta como gobernador de Nayarit|url=http://www.milenio.com/cdb/doc/noticias2011/ae325c6da7214b308bcd1dc444cf0275|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110923230925/http://www.milenio.com/cdb/doc/noticias2011/ae325c6da7214b308bcd1dc444cf0275|dead-url=yes|archive-date=23 September 2011|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=Milenio|date=19 September 2011}}</ref> He also served as Municipal President of [[Tepic]] between 2008 and 2011.<ref>{{cite news|last=Vargas|first=Ramón|title=Roberto Sandoval ya tiene su gabinete|url=http://www.periodicoexpress.com.mx/nota.php?id=209961|accessdate=25 April 2014|newspaper=Periodico Express|date=13 August 2008}}</ref>

The [[United States Department of the Treasury]] declared Roberto Sandoval Castañeda and judge Isidro Avelar Gutiérrez "significant drug dealers" on May 17, 2019. Six other individuals and six corporations were similarly sanctioned.<ref>{{citation |url=https://www.proceso.com.mx/584518/eu-pone-en-lista-negra-a-exgobernador-y-a-magistrado-senala-ligas-con-el-cjng|title=EU pone en lista negra a exgobernador y a magistrado; señala ligas con el CJNG|publisher=Proceso|date=May 17, 2019|accessdate=May 20, 2019 |language=Spanish|trans-title=US blacklists former governor and magistrate; points to leagues with the CJNG}}</ref>

